id: pm-oe33
title: "Feature: Extensibility architecture verified - governance, custom types, agent UX"
description: "Extensibility assessment: governance presets (minimal/default/strict/custom) switch correctly. Custom type options require pre-defined schema (enforced). Status aliases normalize correctly. Error envelopes in JSON include actionable guidance with examples. pm contracts provides complete machine-readable API surface. Definition of done criteria are configurable. Extension lifecycle is complete (install/manage/doctor/init/explore/activate/uninstall)."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[5]: agent-ux,audit,extensibility,pm-cli,verification
created_at: "2026-05-01T18:05:11.750Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-01T18:07:11.917Z"
author: audit-agent
acceptance_criteria: "Governance presets, error envelopes, and extension lifecycle are fully verified"
parent: pm-2eb3
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-2eb3,parent,"2026-05-01T18:05:11.750Z",audit-agent,null
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-01T18:05:11.750Z",audit-agent,"Evidence: strict governance mode adds required fields. Error envelopes with --json include URN-typed errors. pm contracts --schema-only --action create --json provides full parameter schema. pm help --json provides structured help v1 format. All commands accept --json."
close_reason: "Extensibility verified: governance presets work, type schema enforcement works, JSON error envelopes have actionable guidance, pm contracts provides v4 API schema, extension lifecycle complete"
body: "Key findings: (1) Governance preset switching works. (2) Type options are schema-enforced. (3) JSON error envelopes consistently include type/code/title/detail/required/why/examples/next_steps. (4) pm contracts --json provides v4 schema with full flag metadata. (5) pm completion generates bash/zsh scripts. (6) Extension scaffold produces working projects. (7) Agent-friendly: all output is deterministic TOON/JSON, all commands have --json, errors have examples. (8) Non-software adaptability: custom types via settings work, but type_options require extension registration for runtime schema."
